    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 1454,
      "versionNonce": 1419270889,
      "index": "a7",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "noSLhjSB5rcSMUaQhqXvG",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 239.7180467288165,
      "y": 404.83203125,
      "strokeColor": "#000000",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "width": 574.9757690429688,
      "height": 1080,
      "seed": 2106729880,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [
        {
          "id": "QemsyXvBN5DdjoVxr5f9b",
          "type": "arrow"
        }
      ],
      "updated": 1720053704996,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "text": "Functional\n- Query top-k videos (max 1000)\n- 1 hour, 1 day, 1 month, all time\n\n---- Out of scope----\n- no arbitrary time periods\nno arbitrary starting point\n\nnon-Functional\n- <1 min staleness\n- no approximation\n- massive num of views\n- massive num of videos\n- Result in 10-100 ms\n- Economical\n\nScale Estimation\n - Throughput\n   if we have a 10B views per day\n    (10B views/day) / (100k sec/day)\n    = 1M TPS\n\n - Storage\n   * videos/day \n     = ( (60mins content/sec) / (6 min content/video) ) * 100K sec/day \n     = 1M videos/day\n   * Total videos = 1M * 365days * 10yrs \n                  = 3.6B or ~4B\n\n   * With this calculation the size (Naive) of \n      table ID and Count would be (count is views for each videoID),\n\n     Storage = 4B * (8 bytes/ID + 8 bytes/count)\n              = 64GB\n     \n     Ok, probably something we can keep in memory, \n     especially if we use a number of hosts.\n\n  \n- Core Entities\n  1. View\n  2. Video\n  3. TimeWindow\n\n- API\n  GET view/top?window={WINDOW}&k={K}\n  \n\n\n   \n   \n\n\n",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Functional\n- Query top-k videos (max 1000)\n- 1 hour, 1 day, 1 month, all time\n\n---- Out of scope----\n- no arbitrary time periods\nno arbitrary starting point\n\nnon-Functional\n- <1 min staleness\n- no approximation\n- massive num of views\n- massive num of videos\n- Result in 10-100 ms\n- Economical\n\nScale Estimation\n - Throughput\n   if we have a 10B views per day\n    (10B views/day) / (100k sec/day)\n    = 1M TPS\n\n - Storage\n   * videos/day \n     = ( (60mins content/sec) / (6 min content/video) ) * 100K sec/day \n     = 1M videos/day\n   * Total videos = 1M * 365days * 10yrs \n                  = 3.6B or ~4B\n\n   * With this calculation the size (Naive) of \n      table ID and Count would be (count is views for each videoID),\n\n     Storage = 4B * (8 bytes/ID + 8 bytes/count)\n              = 64GB\n     \n     Ok, probably something we can keep in memory, \n     especially if we use a number of hosts.\n\n  \n- Core Entities\n  1. View\n  2. Video\n  3. TimeWindow\n\n- API\n  GET view/top?window={WINDOW}&k={K}\n  \n\n\n   \n   \n\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
