      "originalText": "Design a Web Crawler",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 998,
      "versionNonce": 32334009,
      "index": "b0m",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "pFlKXa0L3CDqHLj5jI8Hc",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 163.21930203684542,
      "y": 2680.5061210929994,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "width": 876.5115966796875,
      "height": 1505,
      "seed": 1996704345,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [
        {
          "id": "KWWBVDTxEjcrc_cR82uhV",
          "type": "arrow"
        }
      ],
      "updated": 1720757012845,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "text": "Functional Req:\n- Crawl the web starting from seed URLs.\n- Extract text data and store\n----below the line---\n- actual processing data\n- Handling non-text data (e.g., images, videos, etc.).\n- Handling of dynamic content (e.g., JavaScript-rendered pages).\n- Handling of authentication (e.g., login-required pages)\n\nScale: \n- 10B web pages\n- Page size: 2MB each\n- 5 days to scrape\n- unlimited resource (within reason running cost)\n\nNon-functional Req: \n- Fault tolerance \n- Politeness\n- Efficiency to crawl the web in under 5 days.\n- Scalability to handle 10B pages.\n\n---Below the line (out of scope)---\n- Security\n- operating cost\n- adhere to legal requirements\n\nCore Entties: \n- Text data\n- URL Metadata\n- Domain metadata\n\nAPI or Interface: \n- input: set of seed urls\n- output: website data\n\nData FLow: \n1. take the seed URL from fontier and\nget the IP from DNS\n2. Fetch HTML\n3. Extract text from HTML\n4. Store text in DB \n5. Extract the urls in the text and add to frontier\n6. Repeat steps 1 to 5",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Functional Req:\n- Crawl the web starting from seed URLs.\n- Extract text data and store\n----below the line---\n- actual processing data\n- Handling non-text data (e.g., images, videos, etc.).\n- Handling of dynamic content (e.g., JavaScript-rendered pages).\n- Handling of authentication (e.g., login-required pages)\n\nScale: \n- 10B web pages\n- Page size: 2MB each\n- 5 days to scrape\n- unlimited resource (within reason running cost)\n\nNon-functional Req: \n- Fault tolerance \n- Politeness\n- Efficiency to crawl the web in under 5 days.\n- Scalability to handle 10B pages.\n\n---Below the line (out of scope)---\n- Security\n- operating cost\n- adhere to legal requirements\n\nCore Entties: \n- Text data\n- URL Metadata\n- Domain metadata\n\nAPI or Interface: \n- input: set of seed urls\n- output: website data\n\nData FLow: \n1. take the seed URL from fontier and\nget the IP from DNS\n2. Fetch HTML\n3. Extract text from HTML\n4. Store text in DB \n5. Extract the urls in the text and add to frontier\n6. Repeat steps 1 to 5",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
