    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 1255,
      "versionNonce": 1696405920,
      "index": "b5z",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "PHBuVIIneTIbRdLnoFblx",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 2002.816404495174,
      "y": 11045.591704615157,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "width": 1582.5250525446947,
      "height": 1292.7274090114454,
      "seed": 291787273,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1723577187070,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 41.36727708836625,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "Workflow with Multiple Kafka Topics\n\nIngestion/Chunking Queue:\n - Incoming video streams are published to this topic by the media server.\n\nChunking Stage: \n- Consumes from the chunking queue and Divide video streams into smaller \nchunks.\n\nSegmenting Stage:\n - SegmentingWorker: Consumes from the SegmentingQueue.\n - Segmenting Output: Process chunks into precise segments.\n\nTranscoding Stage:\n - TranscodingWorker: Consumes from the Transcoding Queue.\n - Transcoding Output: Convert segments into multiple resolutions and \n    bitrates.\n\nABR Packaging Stage:\n - ABR Packaging Worker: Consumes from the ABR Packaging queue.\n - ABR Packaging Output: \n        * Package segments for adaptive bitrate streaming.\n        * Create Manifest files and store in S3.\n        * Store metadata about video segments to DDB (this could be direct \nREST call, i.e. another service that takes the metadata and store in DDb) ",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Workflow with Multiple Kafka Topics\n\nIngestion/Chunking Queue:\n - Incoming video streams are published to this topic by the media server.\n\nChunking Stage: \n- Consumes from the chunking queue and Divide video streams into smaller chunks.\n\nSegmenting Stage:\n - SegmentingWorker: Consumes from the SegmentingQueue.\n - Segmenting Output: Process chunks into precise segments.\n\nTranscoding Stage:\n - TranscodingWorker: Consumes from the Transcoding Queue.\n - Transcoding Output: Convert segments into multiple resolutions and \n    bitrates.\n\nABR Packaging Stage:\n - ABR Packaging Worker: Consumes from the ABR Packaging queue.\n - ABR Packaging Output: \n        * Package segments for adaptive bitrate streaming.\n        * Create Manifest files and store in S3.\n        * Store metadata about video segments to DDB (this could be direct REST call, i.e. another service that takes the metadata and store in DDb) ",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 464,
      "versionNonce": 1565070361,
      "index": "b60",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "kHVYZg0zRAbMDGzzmTJYF",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 4975.265929214009,
      "y": 10969.603621231341,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "width": 748.187744140625,
      "height": 1215,
      "seed": 331423799,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1722446546898,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "   IoT Devices Stream Data (RTSP)\n             ↓\n      Load Balancer\n             ↓\n   Media Ingestion Nodes (Media server)\n             ↓\n         Chunking\n             ↓\n       Segmentation\n             ↓\n       Transcoding\n             ↓\n       ABR Packaging\n             ↓\n      ┌──────┐\n      │  Object     │\n      │  Storage   │\n      └──────┘\n             ↓\n      Metadata Storage (REST)\n             ↓\n  Client Requests Playback (REST)\n             ↓\n      Content Delivery Network (CDN)\n             ↓\n   Adaptive Bit Rate Streaming\n",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "   IoT Devices Stream Data (RTSP)\n             ↓\n      Load Balancer\n             ↓\n   Media Ingestion Nodes (Media server)\n             ↓\n         Chunking\n             ↓\n       Segmentation\n             ↓\n       Transcoding\n             ↓\n       ABR Packaging\n             ↓\n      ┌──────┐\n      │  Object     │\n      │  Storage   │\n      └──────┘\n             ↓\n      Metadata Storage (REST)\n             ↓\n  Client Requests Playback (REST)\n             ↓\n      Content Delivery Network (CDN)\n             ↓\n   Adaptive Bit Rate Streaming\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
