    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 257,
      "versionNonce": 2067479993,
      "index": "bAF",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "9m6B2SE0XucXXBSslTx8D",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 2615.8054332026486,
      "y": 21992.630775512866,
      "strokeColor": "#2f9e44",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "width": 2330.009307861328,
      "height": 1493.6364892585618,
      "seed": 57630393,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1727672198646,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 51.952573539428236,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "Elasticsearch plays a crucial role in the food delivery system design, \nprimarily serving as a powerful search and analytics engine. \nIts purpose is to provide fast, scalable, and efficient search capabilities\nfor restaurants, menu items, and related information. \n\nPurpose of Elasticsearch in the Food Delivery System: \n1. Fast and Efficient Searching: Elasticsearch enables quick and relevant \n   search results for users looking for restaurants, cuisines, or specific dishes.\n\n2. Real-time Updates: It allows for near real-time updates of restaurant \n   information, menus, and prices, ensuring customers always see the most current data.\n\n3. Complex Querying: Elasticsearch supports complex queries, including geospatial \n   searches, which are crucial for finding nearby restaurants or determining delivery areas.\n\n4. Scalability: It can handle large volumes of data and high concurrent searches, which \n    is essential for a food delivery platform with millions of users and restaurants.\n\n5. Faceted Search: Elasticsearch facilitates faceted search, allowing users to filter \n   results by cuisine type, price range, ratings, etc.\n\n6. Fuzzy Matching: It can handle typos and provide relevant results even when search \n   terms are not exact matches.",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Elasticsearch plays a crucial role in the food delivery system design, \nprimarily serving as a powerful search and analytics engine. \nIts purpose is to provide fast, scalable, and efficient search capabilities\nfor restaurants, menu items, and related information. \n\nPurpose of Elasticsearch in the Food Delivery System: \n1. Fast and Efficient Searching: Elasticsearch enables quick and relevant \n   search results for users looking for restaurants, cuisines, or specific dishes.\n\n2. Real-time Updates: It allows for near real-time updates of restaurant \n   information, menus, and prices, ensuring customers always see the most current data.\n\n3. Complex Querying: Elasticsearch supports complex queries, including geospatial \n   searches, which are crucial for finding nearby restaurants or determining delivery areas.\n\n4. Scalability: It can handle large volumes of data and high concurrent searches, which \n    is essential for a food delivery platform with millions of users and restaurants.\n\n5. Faceted Search: Elasticsearch facilitates faceted search, allowing users to filter \n   results by cuisine type, price range, ratings, etc.\n\n6. Fuzzy Matching: It can handle typos and provide relevant results even when search \n   terms are not exact matches.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 72,
      "versionNonce": 1985768247,
      "index": "bAG",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "r4XeDkJDlUWQngJFynCPv",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 6709.055000625342,
      "y": 18150.475506763563,
      "strokeColor": "#f08c00",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "width": 1710.511474609375,
      "height": 254.24982824135998,
      "seed": 1332387255,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1727671916874,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 50.849965648272,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "Elasticsearch plays a crucial role in the food delivery system design, \nprimarily serving as a powerful search and analytics engine. \nIts purpose is to provide fast, scalable, and efficient search \ncapabilities for restaurants, menu items, and related information. ",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Elasticsearch plays a crucial role in the food delivery system design, \nprimarily serving as a powerful search and analytics engine. \nIts purpose is to provide fast, scalable, and efficient search \ncapabilities for restaurants, menu items, and related information. ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 182,
      "versionNonce": 838060427,
      "index": "bAI",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "nok4OlMEw1oiQyKjhnmt_",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 4505.171638798656,
      "y": 19366.370284452714,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "width": 2370.0728912353516,
      "height": 1553.5475779381309,
      "seed": 1306509113,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1730235980455,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 49.71352249402019,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "Real-Time Tracking DB (NoSQL):\nThe Real-Time Tracking DB stores dynamic, unstructured data such as the GPS coordinates \nof delivery drivers. Since driver locations change frequently, a NoSQL database is preferred \nover traditional relational databases because it can handle high-frequency updates, offers \nflexibility with unstructured data, and is highly scalable for large datasets.\n\nPopular NoSQL Databases in the Market:\n\n* Redis: An in-memory key-value store often used as a cache, but it \n    can also manage real-time tracking if combined with geospatial \n    extensions like RedisGeo, which supports storing and querying location-based data.\n\n * MongoDB: A widely-used document-based NoSQL database, offering \n    excellent support for geospatial queries, which are essential for tracking locations.\n\n * Cassandra: A highly scalable NoSQL database, optimized for write-heavy \n   workloads and capable of handling massive amounts of data. Ideal for \n   real-time tracking in large systems like Uber Eats.\n\n * Firebase Realtime Database: A NoSQL cloud database offered by Google, designed \n   for real-time data syncing, commonly used for tracking locations in mobile applications.\n\n * DynamoDB (AWS): [Expensive] A fully managed NoSQL database that offers high performance \n   and scales automatically. Its integration with AWS services makes it a great \n   choice for large-scale real-time tracking systems.",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Real-Time Tracking DB (NoSQL):\nThe Real-Time Tracking DB stores dynamic, unstructured data such as the GPS coordinates \nof delivery drivers. Since driver locations change frequently, a NoSQL database is preferred \nover traditional relational databases because it can handle high-frequency updates, offers \nflexibility with unstructured data, and is highly scalable for large datasets.\n\nPopular NoSQL Databases in the Market:\n\n* Redis: An in-memory key-value store often used as a cache, but it \n    can also manage real-time tracking if combined with geospatial \n    extensions like RedisGeo, which supports storing and querying location-based data.\n\n * MongoDB: A widely-used document-based NoSQL database, offering \n    excellent support for geospatial queries, which are essential for tracking locations.\n\n * Cassandra: A highly scalable NoSQL database, optimized for write-heavy \n   workloads and capable of handling massive amounts of data. Ideal for \n   real-time tracking in large systems like Uber Eats.\n\n * Firebase Realtime Database: A NoSQL cloud database offered by Google, designed \n   for real-time data syncing, commonly used for tracking locations in mobile applications.\n\n * DynamoDB (AWS): [Expensive] A fully managed NoSQL database that offers high performance \n   and scales automatically. Its integration with AWS services makes it a great \n   choice for large-scale real-time tracking systems.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 506,
      "versionNonce": 505371033,
      "index": "bAJ",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "nmlXgJqdvX-kSqcFzd97t",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 5391.0630032899935,
      "y": 21073.619347201853,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "width": 1600.763427734375,
      "height": 3207.8796493895957,
      "seed": 885324089,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1727674952947,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 50.31968077473876,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "*** Design Diagram: Delivery Service Real-Time Tracking Flow ***\n\n+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+\n|                Driver’s Mobile App (GPS)                           |\n|------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| - Sends driver’s GPS coordinates to backend periodically    |\n| - Uses WebSocket / HTTP API to send real-time data      |\n+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+\n                              |\n                              v\n+-------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n|                    WebSocket / HTTP API                          |\n|--------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| - Facilitates real-time data transmission                          |\n| - Receives GPS coordinates and forwards them to backend   |\n+-------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n                              |\n                              v\n+--------------------------------------------------------------------+\n|                  Real-Time Tracking DB (NoSQL)              |\n|----------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| - Stores driver’s current GPS location                        |\n| - Tracks real-time driver status (e.g., Available, On Trip)  |\n| - Supports geospatial queries (e.g., nearby drivers)         |\n+---------------------------------------------------------------------+\n                              |\n                              v\n+---------------------------------------------------------------------+\n|                  Delivery Service                                   |\n|----------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| - Matches available drivers based on proximity               |\n| - Tracks real-time driver location using Real-Time DB      |\n| - Updates Order Service on delivery progress                |\n+---------------------------------------------------------------------+\n                              |\n                              v\n+--------------------------------------------------------------------+\n|                  Map Service (Google Maps API)               |\n|----------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| - Displays real-time driver location on a map                 |\n| - Calculates ETA and route optimization                     |\n+--------------------------------------------------------------------+\n                              |\n                              v\n+----------------------------------------------------------------------+\n|                  Order Service & Notification Service           |\n|-----------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| - Updates order status (Picked Up, Out for Delivery)      |\n| - Sends notifications to customers with delivery updates  |\n+----------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "*** Design Diagram: Delivery Service Real-Time Tracking Flow ***\n\n+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+\n|                Driver’s Mobile App (GPS)                           |\n|------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| - Sends driver’s GPS coordinates to backend periodically    |\n| - Uses WebSocket / HTTP API to send real-time data      |\n+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+\n                              |\n                              v\n+-------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n|                    WebSocket / HTTP API                          |\n|--------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| - Facilitates real-time data transmission                          |\n| - Receives GPS coordinates and forwards them to backend   |\n+-------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n                              |\n                              v\n+--------------------------------------------------------------------+\n|                  Real-Time Tracking DB (NoSQL)              |\n|----------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| - Stores driver’s current GPS location                        |\n| - Tracks real-time driver status (e.g., Available, On Trip)  |\n| - Supports geospatial queries (e.g., nearby drivers)         |\n+---------------------------------------------------------------------+\n                              |\n                              v\n+---------------------------------------------------------------------+\n|                  Delivery Service                                   |\n|----------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| - Matches available drivers based on proximity               |\n| - Tracks real-time driver location using Real-Time DB      |\n| - Updates Order Service on delivery progress                |\n+---------------------------------------------------------------------+\n                              |\n                              v\n+--------------------------------------------------------------------+\n|                  Map Service (Google Maps API)               |\n|----------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| - Displays real-time driver location on a map                 |\n| - Calculates ETA and route optimization                     |\n+--------------------------------------------------------------------+\n                              |\n                              v\n+----------------------------------------------------------------------+\n|                  Order Service & Notification Service           |\n|-----------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| - Updates order status (Picked Up, Out for Delivery)      |\n| - Sends notifications to customers with delivery updates  |\n+----------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
