      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "Stock Price Change Notifications/Alerts",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Stock Price Change Notifications/Alerts",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 529,
      "versionNonce": 1048727815,
      "index": "bAj",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "72pc5qPfpjXESY3k-wjsW",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": -19.250664073102598,
      "y": 26940.830156740376,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "width": 1766.7520857449263,
      "height": 1355.6902946264704,
      "seed": 57810119,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1728525747034,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 60.252901983398594,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "** Non-Functional Requirements ** \n- Scalability: System should handle millions of rules and \n  thousands of stock updates per second.\n\n- Low Latency: Notifications should be sent to users \n  within one minute.\n\n- High Availability: System must remain available during \n  high traffic or stock market volatility.\n\n- Fault Tolerance: The system should be resilient to \n  failures in external stock APIs and notification services.\n\n- Data Consistency: Rules and stock data must remain \n  consistent even in a distributed setup.\n\n- Security: Users' data and subscriptions must be secured, \n  particularly notifications and stock preferences.",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "** Non-Functional Requirements ** \n- Scalability: System should handle millions of rules and \n  thousands of stock updates per second.\n\n- Low Latency: Notifications should be sent to users \n  within one minute.\n\n- High Availability: System must remain available during \n  high traffic or stock market volatility.\n\n- Fault Tolerance: The system should be resilient to \n  failures in external stock APIs and notification services.\n\n- Data Consistency: Rules and stock data must remain \n  consistent even in a distributed setup.\n\n- Security: Users' data and subscriptions must be secured, \n  particularly notifications and stock preferences.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 265,
      "versionNonce": 1697139783,
      "index": "bAk",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "fldlyzLMwwISLRkpzUM7p",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": -27.291132974569337,
      "y": 28537.414388323406,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "width": 1861.77978515625,
      "height": 1173.8478781806637,
      "seed": 2053921001,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1728525756644,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 55.23990014967833,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "** Back-of-the-Envelope Estimation **\n- Users: Assume 10 million users, each tracking 10 stocks.\n\n- Rules: 1 million users may define 3 rules per stock, l\n    eading to 30 million rules to scan.\n\n- Stock Data: With ~5000 stocks, receiving updates every \n   sec for price changes, that’s around 5000 updates per sec.\n\n- Notification Throughput: 1% of rules trigger notifications \n  per minute (10,000 notifications/min).\n\n- Storage: Each rule can take 200 bytes, resulting in ~6GB \n  of storage for all user rules.\n\n- Latency: Each rule check and notification should occur within 1 sec.\n",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "** Back-of-the-Envelope Estimation **\n- Users: Assume 10 million users, each tracking 10 stocks.\n\n- Rules: 1 million users may define 3 rules per stock, l\n    eading to 30 million rules to scan.\n\n- Stock Data: With ~5000 stocks, receiving updates every \n   sec for price changes, that’s around 5000 updates per sec.\n\n- Notification Throughput: 1% of rules trigger notifications \n  per minute (10,000 notifications/min).\n\n- Storage: Each rule can take 200 bytes, resulting in ~6GB \n  of storage for all user rules.\n\n- Latency: Each rule check and notification should occur within 1 sec.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 562,
      "versionNonce": 1748068649,
      "index": "bAl",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "7BT6Ho0N-VE3Koj7GCTdt",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 38.12987438296568,
      "y": 29881.231014897072,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "width": 1687.4283856563318,
      "height": 2047.5307618348147,
      "seed": 733266537,
      "groupIds": [],
