      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "[Google Doc: Look here for more details: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Hplx3vXIbXQE_rY_1T5rRKDZN4NGvA8lAdWUCiWDHSY/edit?tab=t.0\nUseful Links: https://bugfree.ai/system-design/distributed-job-scheduler\n]",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "[Google Doc: Look here for more details: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Hplx3vXIbXQE_rY_1T5rRKDZN4NGvA8lAdWUCiWDHSY/edit?tab=t.0\nUseful Links: https://bugfree.ai/system-design/distributed-job-scheduler\n]",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 584,
      "versionNonce": 2121515441,
      "index": "bFZ",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "WH9FPeG59v0Mv5nmQ3DYO",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 3048.8227181203324,
      "y": 45978.6371731159,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "width": 695.7715454101562,
      "height": 431.1036814850705,
      "seed": 1190947949,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1754711944221,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 34.48829451880564,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "- Execute jobs by picking from queue. \n- Each worker updates job status in \n  the DB (success/fail).\n- Interacts with the queue to pull tasks \n  and with DB to update job statuses.\n- Workers should be stateless to enable \n  horizontal scaling. \n- Use thread pools within workers for \n  parallel job execution.\n- Logs to log storage.",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- Execute jobs by picking from queue. \n- Each worker updates job status in \n  the DB (success/fail).\n- Interacts with the queue to pull tasks \n  and with DB to update job statuses.\n- Workers should be stateless to enable \n  horizontal scaling. \n- Use thread pools within workers for \n  parallel job execution.\n- Logs to log storage.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 666,
      "versionNonce": 1657955217,
      "index": "bFb",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "nff7FLzXT1bxdE8NGyQrd",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 3824.9010705574674,
      "y": 46417.577524340086,
      "strokeColor": "#f08c00",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "width": 936.0658272678032,
      "height": 1080,
      "seed": 1303463661,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1754711944221,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "Why Separate Databases?\n- Different Access Patterns: \n    Job storage requires frequent reads, updates, \n    and transactions, while log storage is write-heavy\n    with occasional reads, often in the form of batch\nanalysis.\n    \n- Optimized for Different Workloads: \n    Using a database like PostgreSQL or Redis for\njob storage\n    ensures fast job updates and queries, while\nElasticsearch or\n    InfluxDB for log storage allowsfor efficient log\nindexing,\n    searching, and analysis.\n\n- Scalability Considerations: \n    Using different databases allows each system to\nscale independently.\n    Log storage systems like Elasticsearch can scale\nhorizontally as the\n    log volume grows, while job storage can focus on\nmaintaining consistency\n    and fast access times.",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Why Separate Databases?\n- Different Access Patterns: \n    Job storage requires frequent reads, updates, \n    and transactions, while log storage is write-heavy \n    with occasional reads, often in the form of batch analysis.\n    \n- Optimized for Different Workloads: \n    Using a database like PostgreSQL or Redis for job storage \n    ensures fast job updates and queries, while Elasticsearch or \n    InfluxDB for log storage allowsfor efficient log indexing, \n    searching, and analysis.\n\n- Scalability Considerations: \n    Using different databases allows each system to scale independently. \n    Log storage systems like Elasticsearch can scale horizontally as the \n    log volume grows, while job storage can focus on maintaining consistency \n    and fast access times.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 1056,
      "versionNonce": 1791084913,
      "index": "bFd",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "gHQB4e9hp59gjJpGiN3A5",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 1850.6676823853613,
      "y": 45669.69101106983,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "width": 592.1997585296631,
      "height": 315,
      "seed": 459262027,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1754711944221,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "- Consumes from Kafka \n   topic (CDC events)\n- Parses CDC events to \n  detect job changes\n- Applies scheduling rules, \n  prioritizes jobs, and assigns \n  jobs to available Worker Nodes ",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- Consumes from Kafka \n   topic (CDC events)\n- Parses CDC events to \n  detect job changes\n- Applies scheduling rules, \n  prioritizes jobs, and assigns \n  jobs to available Worker Nodes ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
