      "text": "Ingest Gateway\n- Auth\n- Rate-limit\n- Handle Idenpotency\n- Load Shading\n- secure transport",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Ingest Gateway\n- Auth\n- Rate-limit\n- Handle Idenpotency\n- Load Shading\n- secure transport",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "WnoA0DuHKGXzE6hRjLT4O",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 640.3244503781466,
      "y": 56059.7849529195,
      "width": 1699.4326927034908,
      "height": 630.3393481824093,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#f08c00",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bIC",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 541942824,
      "version": 523,
      "versionNonce": 119734104,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1756082036548,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "\"The Ingest Gateway is not the same as a general-purpose\nAPI Gateway. While an API Gateway handles user-facing API\ncalls for dashboards, alert rules, or queries, the Ingest\nGateway is specialized for high-throughput telemetry\ningestion. It validates, deduplicates, batches, and securely\nforwards metrics into the pipeline. For example,\nOpenTelemetry Collector or Cortex/Mimir Ingest Gateway is\nbest suited here. This separation allows us to scale the\nmetrics ingestion independently from the control-plane APIs.\"",
      "fontSize": 56.03016428288085,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\"The Ingest Gateway is not the same as a general-purpose API Gateway. While an API Gateway handles user-facing API calls for dashboards, alert rules, or queries, the Ingest Gateway is specialized for high-throughput telemetry ingestion. It validates, deduplicates, batches, and securely forwards metrics into the pipeline. For example, OpenTelemetry Collector or Cortex/Mimir Ingest Gateway is best suited here. This separation allows us to scale the metrics ingestion independently from the control-plane APIs.\"",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
