    {
      "id": "VitS4ztk-l1BbBALPyTSP",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1367.5844220310978,
      "y": 63769.39064061389,
      "width": 766.6197509765625,
      "height": 450,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bJz",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 494385240,
      "version": 322,
      "versionNonce": 1430669608,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [
        {
          "id": "PVoTgk_hvBZ6dg7u_tQmd",
          "type": "arrow"
        }
      ],
      "updated": 1756136116488,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- Normalize query terms (tokenization, \n  stemming, etc., same as ingestion pipeline).\n- Collect term stats (document frequency) \n   to plan execution.\n - Fan-out sub-queries to the underlying \n   storage (OpenSearch).\n- Merge results → intersect postings lists \n   (since requirement is AND semantics).\n- Apply filters (visibility, time ranges).\n- Return post IDs with pagination.",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- Normalize query terms (tokenization, \n  stemming, etc., same as ingestion pipeline).\n- Collect term stats (document frequency) \n   to plan execution.\n - Fan-out sub-queries to the underlying \n   storage (OpenSearch).\n- Merge results → intersect postings lists \n   (since requirement is AND semantics).\n- Apply filters (visibility, time ranges).\n- Return post IDs with pagination.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "bXTvyDBeLD1biKbNBa9KL",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1328.6357840224364,
      "y": 64288.183828669076,
      "width": 1526.9755859375,
      "height": 990,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#f08c00",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bK0",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 675054168,
      "version": 171,
      "versionNonce": 792858456,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1756136116183,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Interview-ready script: \n“The Query Service is the coordinator. Clients hit this instead of going \ndirectly to OpenSearch. It first normalizes the query terms using the same \nanalyzer as ingestion — so query tokens match index tokens. Then it fetches \nterm statistics: for hot terms we use Redis cache; otherwise we call \nOpenSearch. Based on DF, we plan to intersect the smallest postings list \nfirst to minimize work.\n\nFor example, if the query is [‘search’, ‘system’], Redis tells us ‘system’ is \nrarer than ‘search’. We fetch postings for both, then intersect them. \nAt this point we apply a visibility filter — powered by a deny-bitmap service \n— so posts deleted or private are immediately excluded. Finally, we paginate \nand return post IDs.\n\nDirectly, Query Service talks to:\n- Clients for requests/responses\n- Redis for DF and hot postings cache\n- OpenSearch for main postings lists\n- Visibility filter service for access control.\n\nThis separation keeps query latency predictable (<100ms P99), while ensuring \nprivacy is never violated and allowing us to scale query and index layers independently.”",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Interview-ready script: \n“The Query Service is the coordinator. Clients hit this instead of going \ndirectly to OpenSearch. It first normalizes the query terms using the same \nanalyzer as ingestion — so query tokens match index tokens. Then it fetches \nterm statistics: for hot terms we use Redis cache; otherwise we call \nOpenSearch. Based on DF, we plan to intersect the smallest postings list \nfirst to minimize work.\n\nFor example, if the query is [‘search’, ‘system’], Redis tells us ‘system’ is \nrarer than ‘search’. We fetch postings for both, then intersect them. \nAt this point we apply a visibility filter — powered by a deny-bitmap service \n— so posts deleted or private are immediately excluded. Finally, we paginate \nand return post IDs.\n\nDirectly, Query Service talks to:\n- Clients for requests/responses\n- Redis for DF and hot postings cache\n- OpenSearch for main postings lists\n- Visibility filter service for access control.\n\nThis separation keeps query latency predictable (<100ms P99), while ensuring \nprivacy is never violated and allowing us to scale query and index layers independently.”",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
